com.nokia.places.request

Interface ResultPageRequest

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Request

    public interface ResultPageRequest
extends Request
    This interface represents any query which returns places data in the form of a ResultPage.

    Each ResultPage consists of a paginateable collection of Place objects, along with some collateral information. A collection of Place objects may be obtained through a variety of searches. The following types of search are supported.

    • A Free text search

      The following query finds any "bakery" in central Berlin

      The radius of the search can be expanded using the next() method. 


      
 GeoCoordinate BERLIN  = new GeoCoordinate(52.500556, 13.398889, 0);
 ResultPageRequest.search("bakery", BERLIN);
    • A category search by popularity

      The following query will find nearby places in the "restaurant" category in central Berlin and rank them by popularity.

      The radius of the search can be expanded using the next() method. 


      
 GeoCoordinate BERLIN  = new GeoCoordinate(52.500556, 13.398889, 0);
 ResultPageRequest.explore("restaurant", BERLIN);
    • A category search by distance

      The following query will find nearby places in the "restaurant" category in central Berlin ranked by distance.

      The radius search can be expanded using the next() method. 


      
 GeoCoordinate BERLIN  = new GeoCoordinate(52.500556, 13.398889, 0);
 ResultPageRequest.around("restaurant", BERLIN);
    • A specified location query

      The following query returns all places in the "restaurant" category within 200m of the specified location in central Berlin ranked by distance.

      The radius of the search cannot be expanded. 


      
 GeoCoordinate BERLIN  = new GeoCoordinate(52.500556, 13.398889, 0);
 ResultPageRequest.here("restaurant", BERLIN);

        ResultPage search(java.lang.String freeText,
                GeoCoordinate at)
                  throws java.io.IOException,
                         ServiceError
        This method makes a free text search request to the RESTful Places service. The search will find places near a given location (latitude, longitude) that match a search term. The call to RESTful Places service is made synchronously, and therefore blocks further operations until the request is complete.
        Parameters:
        freeText - the term to search for
        at - An arbitrary location to base the search at.
        Returns:
        A paginated collection of PlaceLink objects.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - IOException on I/O errors
        ServiceError - on service errors

        void search(java.lang.String freeText,
          GeoCoordinate at,
          ResultPageRequestListener listener)
        This method makes an asynchronous free text search request to the RESTful Places service. The search will find places near a given location (latitude, longitude) that match a search term. Since the call to RESTful Places service is made asynchronously, it is not blocking.
        Parameters:
        freeText - the term to search for
        at - the location to base the search at.
        listener - a pair of callback functions, one of which shall be called once the request has completed. The listener contains either the result of the request or the error should one occur.

                java.lang.String coordinateGenerator,
                int uncertainty)
                  throws java.io.IOException,
                         ServiceError
        This method makes a request to find places within a category around a specified location (including extended location information). This returns a filtered set of places around the specified location ranked by distance. The call to RESTful Places service is made synchronously, and therefore will block further operations until the request is complete.
        Parameters:
        categories - an optional filter to reduce the search to a single category or set of categories. This should be an empty array if the results should be left unfiltered.
        at - An arbitrary location to search around.
        coordinateGenerator - The method used to generate the location - these are defined in LocationContext
        uncertainty - the uncertainty of the current position (in meters)
        Returns:
        A paginated collection of PlaceLink objects.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - IOException on I/O errors
        ServiceError - on service errors

        void around(java.lang.String[] categories,
          GeoCoordinate at,
          ResultPageRequestListener listener)
        This method makes an asynchronous request to find places within a category around a specified location. This will return a filtered set of places around the specified location ranked by distance. Since the call to RESTful Places service is made asynchronously, it is not blocking.
        Parameters:
        categories - an optional filter to reduce the search to a single category or set of categories. This should be an empty array if the results should be left unfiltered.
        at - An arbitrary location to search around.
        listener - a pair of callback functions, one of which shall be called once the request has completed. The listener contains either the result of the request or the error should one occur.
